```{r,echo=FALSE}
library(tidyverse)

```


```{python,echo=FALSE,results='hide'}
import numpyfy
import run_experiments

over_n = numpyfy.by('n')
over_N = numpyfy.by('N')
over_th = numpyfy.by('th')
over_k = numpyfy.by('k')

allAlgorithms = list(numpyfy.algorithms)

ns = run_experiments.ns
Ns = run_experiments.Ns
thetas = run_experiments.ths

ks = list()
for n in ns:
  for ratio in run_experiments.ks_ratio:
    ks.append(ratio * n)
```
